pingball.grammars

Class BoardGrammarCreatorListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • pingball.grammars.BoardGrammarBaseListener
      • pingball.grammars.BoardGrammarCreatorListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeListener, BoardGrammarListener

    public class BoardGrammarCreatorListener
extends BoardGrammarBaseListener
    Child class of BoardGrammarBaseListener.java, which is auto-created by ANTLR. In this class, the methods define what happens as the listener walks through the tree. As it exits a node or branch of the tree, the board, gadgets, or balls are created. The gadgets and balls are also added to the board.
    Author:
    Natasha

      Parses through the section containing square bumpers and creates and adds them to the board based on the parsed locations, given there are no gadgets with the same name that have already been added.
      void exitTriBumperLine(BoardGrammarParser.TriBumperLineContext ctx)
      Parses through triangular bumpers and adds them to the board, one at a time, given that the name of the bumper hasn't appeared on the board yet.

      • exitBoardLine

        public void exitBoardLine(BoardGrammarParser.BoardLineContext ctx)
        Parses through the section defining the board's name, and possibly gravity, mu, and/or mu2. If the gravity, mu, and/or mu2 aren't specified, they are defaulted to 25.0, 0.025, and 0.025 respectively. A 20x20 board is created.
